, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFC3FFD5FD44F946BCABC9C2" authority="Juel" authorityName="Juel" box="[741,926,1706,1732]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Puccinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="16" pageNumber="237" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="rupestris">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC3FFD5FD44F946BC52C9C2" box="[741,871,1707,1732]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="237">P. rupestris</emphasis>
Juel
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFC3FFD5FC7BF946BB94C9C2" authority="Juel" authorityName="Juel" box="[986,1185,1706,1732]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Puccinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="16" pageNumber="237" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="vaginatae">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC3FFD5FC7BF946BB52C9C2" box="[986,1127,1707,1732]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="237">P. vaginatae</emphasis>
Juel
</taxonomicName>
, have been reported as heteroecious species alternating between 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC3FFD5FDC5F922BDE3C9EF" box="[612,726,1743,1769]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="237">Sausurrea</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFC3FFD5FCB2F922BC63C9EF" box="[787,854,1743,1769]" class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Carex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="16" pageNumber="237" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC3FFD5FCB2F922BC63C9EF" box="[787,854,1743,1769]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="237">Carex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B74FFC3FFD5FCC9F923BCE9C9EE" author="Juel, O." box="[872,988,1742,1768]" pageId="16" pageNumber="237" pagination="51 - 57" refId="ref20349" refString="Juel, O. (1893) Om nagra heteroeciska Uredineer. Botaniska Notiser 1892 - 1893: 51 - 57." type="journal article" year="1893">Juel 1893</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B74FFC3FFD5FC4BF923BB4AC9EF" author="Jorstad, I." box="[1002,1151,1742,1769]" pageId="16" pageNumber="237" pagination="1 - 28" refId="ref20323" refString="Jorstad, I. (1954) The rust on Cyperaceae and Iridaceae in Norway. Skrifter Norske Vidensk Akademie 1954: 1 - 28." type="journal article" year="1954">Jørstad 1954</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B74FFC3FFD5FB2CF923BA92C9EE" author="Kakishima, M. &amp; Sato, S." box="[1165,1447,1742,1768]" pageId="16" pageNumber="237" pagination="35 - 45" refId="ref20412" refString="Kakishima, M. &amp; Sato, S. (1980) Three Puccinia species on Carex. Transactions of Mycological Society of Japan 21: 35 - 45." type="journal article" year="1980">Kakishima &amp; Sato 1980</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B74FFC3FFD5FF29F91FBE4AC80A" author="Hiratsuka, N. &amp; Sato, S. &amp; Katsuya, K. &amp; Kakishima, M. &amp; Hiratsuka, Y. &amp; Kaneko, S. &amp; Ono, Y. &amp; Sato, T. &amp; Harada, Y. &amp; Hiratsuka, T. &amp; Nakayama, K." box="[136,383,1778,1805]" pageId="16" pageNumber="237" refId="ref19488" refString="Hiratsuka, N., Sato, S., Katsuya, K., Kakishima, M., Hiratsuka, Y., Kaneko, S., Ono, Y., Sato, T., Harada, Y., Hiratsuka, T. &amp; Nakayama, K. (1992) The rust flora of Japan. Tsukuba-shuppankai, Tsukuba, Japan." type="book" year="1992">
Hiratsuka 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC3FFD5FF5EF91EBE06C80A" box="[255,307,1778,1804]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="237">et al</emphasis>
. 1992
</bibRefCitation>
). Among them, specimens of this clade are morphologically identical with descriptions of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFC3FFD5FA36F91EBFC3C836" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Puccinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="16" pageNumber="237" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="vaginatae">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC3FFD5FA36F91EBFC3C836" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="237">P. vaginatae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B74FFC3FFD5FEBFF8FBBEA9C836" author="Juel, O." box="[286,412,1814,1840]" pageId="16" pageNumber="237" pagination="51 - 57" refId="ref20349" refString="Juel, O. (1893) Om nagra heteroeciska Uredineer. Botaniska Notiser 1892 - 1893: 51 - 57." type="journal article" year="1893">Juel (1893)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B74FFC3FFD5FE71F8FBBD46C837" author="Jorstad, I." box="[464,627,1814,1841]" pageId="16" pageNumber="237" pagination="1 - 28" refId="ref20323" refString="Jorstad, I. (1954) The rust on Cyperaceae and Iridaceae in Norway. Skrifter Norske Vidensk Akademie 1954: 1 - 28." type="journal article" year="1954">Jørstad (1954)</bibRefCitation>
. This species is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFC3FFD5FBF2F8FABBE4C836" box="[1107,1233,1815,1840]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Puccinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="16" pageNumber="237" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="rupestris">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC3FFD5FBF2F8FABBE4C836" box="[1107,1233,1815,1840]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="237">P. rupestris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but different in the presence of spermogonia and the number of urediniospore germ pores. Teliospore size of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFC3FFD5FBCDF8D6BA20C852" box="[1132,1301,1850,1876]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Puccinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="16" pageNumber="237" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="ohsawaensis">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC3FFD5FBCDF8D6BA20C852" box="[1132,1301,1850,1876]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="237">P. ohsawaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is larger than that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFC3FFD5FF75F8B2BDB4C87E" authority="(Kakishima &amp; Sato 1980)" baseAuthorityName="Kakishima &amp; Sato" baseAuthorityYear="1980" box="[212,641,1886,1912]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Puccinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="16" pageNumber="237" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="vaginatae">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC3FFD5FF75F8B2BE69C87E" box="[212,348,1887,1912]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="237">P. vaginatae</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B74FFC3FFD5FEC8F8B3BD4DC87E" author="Kakishima, M. &amp; Sato, S." box="[361,632,1886,1912]" pageId="16" pageNumber="237" pagination="35 - 45" refId="ref20412" refString="Kakishima, M. &amp; Sato, S. (1980) Three Puccinia species on Carex. Transactions of Mycological Society of Japan 21: 35 - 45." type="journal article" year="1980">Kakishima &amp; Sato 1980</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFC3FFD5FD2BF8B2BC54C87E" baseAuthorityName="Kakishima &amp; Sato" baseAuthorityYear="1980" box="[650,865,1887,1912]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Puccinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="16" pageNumber="237" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="vaginatae">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC3FFD5FD2BF8B2BC54C87E" box="[650,865,1887,1912]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="237">Puccinia vaginatae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also morphologically similar and phylogenetically close to 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC3FFD5FF44F86EBED6C89A" box="[229,483,1922,1948]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="237">
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFC3FFD5FF44F86EBEEAC89A" box="[229,479,1922,1948]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Puccinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="16" pageNumber="237" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="caricis-atractylodis">P. caricis-atractylodis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
However, this species has a distinct phylogenetic lineage (
<figureCitation id="13512A00FFC3FFD5FBD0F86FBB86C89A" box="[1137,1203,1922,1948]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[136,229,1761,1783]" captionTargetBox="[138,1449,389,1737]" captionTargetId="figure-110@7.[138,1449,389,1737]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Phylogenetic tree of specimens on Cyperaceae and related host plants constructed by MP method based on ITS+28S regions of rDNA. Bootstrap values of MP and ML are followed by the Bayesian posterior probabilities (Bpp) on the nodes in the topology.Asterisk (*) represents bootstrap values or Bpp less than 50% in the topology. Sample data are shown with voucher specimen number or GenBank accession number, and host plant. Sequence data determined in this study are shown in color. Teliospore shapes are shown in each clade detected, and new species are shown by asterisk (*) on clades. 0, I: Spermogonial and aecial host genus. Asterisk (*) on host plants: Spermogonial and aecial host plants." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6416749" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6416749/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="237">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) and its spermogonial and aecial host is different from that of 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC3FFD5FDE3F84ABC70C8C6" box="[578,837,1958,1984]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="237">
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFC3FFD5FDE3F84ABC74C8C6" box="[578,833,1958,1984]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Puccinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="16" pageNumber="237" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="caricis-atractylodes">P. caricis-atractylodes</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Although 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B74FFC3FFD5FC1DF84BBB97C8C6" author="Zhuang, J. Y. &amp; Wei, S. X. &amp; Wang, Y. C." box="[956,1186,1958,1985]" pageId="16" pageNumber="237" refId="ref22054" refString="Zhuang, J. Y., Wei, S. X. &amp; Wang, Y. C. (1998) Flora fungorum Sinicorum, vol. 10, Uredinales (1). Science Press, Beijing, China." type="book" year="1998">
Zhuang 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC3FFD5FBB9F84ABB7CC8C6" box="[1048,1097,1958,1984]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="237">et al</emphasis>
. (1998)
</bibRefCitation>
reported this species as a doubtful species in 
<collectingCountry id="F37D7615FFC3FFD5FED7F827BE89C8E2" box="[374,444,1994,2020]" name="China" pageId="16" pageNumber="237">China</collectingCountry>
, we confirm its occurrence in 
<collectingCountry id="F37D7615FFC3FFD5FCAFF827BC60C8E2" box="[782,853,1994,2020]" name="China" pageId="16" pageNumber="237">China</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
